title: Email contents: Kelly Mest, May 26-31, 2025, N14

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

Records sufficient to show the following:

1. Contents of emails and attachments highlighted on attached email log released via FOIA N017701-061325. Please remove any duplicates. 

This request is made on behalf of The FOIA Bakery. Because this request is in the public interest for Illinois nonprofit The FOIA Bakery’s work to advocate for public education, please waive any fees in accordance with 5 ILCS § 140/6(c). Feel free to contact me with any questions, or if clarification is needed.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Miriam Bhimani

title: GRAMA Request – Code Enforcement Complaints and Violations

communications.subject: Government Records Access and Management Act Request: GRAMA Request – Code Enforcement Complaints and Violations
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Government Records Access and Management Act, I hereby request the following records:

I respectfully request copies of all code enforcement complaints, notices of violation, or related correspondence issued between August 15, 2024 and August 15, 2025 for the following properties:

859 200 W
865 200 W
873 200 W
208 W 900 S St
218 W 900 S St
226 W 900 S St 
886 Sunflower Dr
882 Sunflower Dr
862 Sunflower Dr
870 Sunflower Dr
876 Sunflower Dr
892 Sunflower Dr
891 Sunflower Dr
875 Sunflower Dr
869 Sunflower Dr
861 Sunflower Dr
881 Sunflower Dr 
885 Sunflower Dr

Please include both citizen-generated and city-initiated complaints, as well as any follow-up notes, photographs, or inspection reports.  Please include the date of the complaint, the general nature of the complaint (e.g., weeds, animals, property condition), and the outcome or resolution, if available.

This request is for general neighborhood research purposes. I am not seeking any personally identifying information about complainants or residents beyond what is already considered a public record.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Private.Citizen
